{"title":"Revel Tirade May Just Make You Fall in Love with Titanium Hardtails","link":"https://bikerumor.com/revel-tirade-titanium-hardtail/","date":1707929329000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-1-Large.jpeg\" alt=\"Revel Bikes Tirade ti hardtail\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-1-Large.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-1-Large-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-1-Large-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-1-Large-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-1-Large-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-1-Large-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>Valentine’s Day. A day of flowers, chocolates, cards, and… titanium hardtails? Why not? Whether a gift for your sweetie or just for yourself, the newest bike in the Revel fleet is a beautiful titanium hardtail that might just steal your heart. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-21-Large.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-21-Large.jpeg\" alt=\"Revel Bikes Tirade ti hardtail\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-21-Large.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-21-Large-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-21-Large-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-21-Large-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-21-Large-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-21-Large-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-12-Large.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-12-Large.jpeg\" alt=\"Revel Bikes Tirade ti hardtail head tube\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-12-Large.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-12-Large-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-12-Large-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-12-Large-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-12-Large-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-12-Large-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-5-Large.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-5-Large.jpeg\" alt=\"Revel Bikes Tirade ti hardtail top tube\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-5-Large.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-5-Large-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-5-Large-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-5-Large-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-5-Large-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-5-Large-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-7-Large.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-7-Large.jpeg\" alt=\"Revel Bikes Tirade ti hardtail head tube\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-7-Large.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-7-Large-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-7-Large-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-7-Large-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-7-Large-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-7-Large-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Like the Why Cycles and Revel Ti bikes before it, the Tirade is built utilizing cold-formed 3/2.5 titanium tubing with 6/4 titanium used for the headtube, BB shell, and dropouts. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-19-Large.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-19-Large.jpeg\" alt=\"Revel Bikes Tirade ti hardtail dropouts\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-19-Large.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-19-Large-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-19-Large-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-19-Large-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-19-Large-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-XX-Outdoor-2.24-19-Large-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In this case, those dropouts are sliding UDH dropouts that offer 17mm of chainstay length adjustment. That opens up the ability to easily convert the Tirade to single speed, though it seems like this time there is no split for belt drive use. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Revel-Tirade-geometry.jpeg\"><img width=\"1200\" height=\"394\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Revel-Tirade-geometry.jpeg\" alt=\"Revel Tirade Geometry\n\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Revel-Tirade-geometry.jpeg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Revel-Tirade-geometry-297x98.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Revel-Tirade-geometry-800x263.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Revel-Tirade-geometry-120x39.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Revel-Tirade-geometry-768x252.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Featuring progressive geometry designed around a 140mm travel suspension fork, the frame includes shorter seat tubes to along for long dropper post use. Key figures include a 74º effective seat tube angle, 64.7º head tube angle, and 467mm reach for a large. Tirades will be offered in Small through XXL sizing with a 522mm reach on the XXL (XL and XXL also get slightly steeper STA).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Tirades run 29″ wheels front and rear, with a claimed frame weight of 2,290g for a large. Frames feature internal cable routing, a threaded bottom bracket, and IS 42/52 integrated headset. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Details and Key Features:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Frame Material: Titanium</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Front Travel: 140mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Wheel Size: 29”</li>\n\n\n\n<li>5 sizes: Small, Medium, Large, XL, XXL</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Frame weight: 2,290g (5.05lbs) size Large</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Size-appropriate seat tube angles. Slightly steeper on XL and XXL</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Shorter seat tubes with long insertion depths to run longer dropper posts</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Internal cable routing – clean, quiet, and simple</li>\n\n\n\n<li>SRAM UDH derailleur hanger</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Sliding Dropouts with 17mm of chainstay length adjustability</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Pricing &amp; Availability</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade_frame_side-Large.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade_frame_side-Large.jpeg\" alt=\"Revel Bikes Tirade ti hardtail\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade_frame_side-Large.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade_frame_side-Large-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade_frame_side-Large-800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade_frame_side-Large-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade_frame_side-Large-768x576.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade_frame_45-Large.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade_frame_45-Large.jpeg\" alt=\"Revel Bikes Tirade ti hardtail frame\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade_frame_45-Large.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade_frame_45-Large-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade_frame_45-Large-800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade_frame_45-Large-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade_frame_45-Large-768x576.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-GX-Production-2.24-1-Large.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-GX-Production-2.24-1-Large.jpeg\" alt=\"Revel Bikes Tirade ti hardtail Gx\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-GX-Production-2.24-1-Large.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-GX-Production-2.24-1-Large-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-GX-Production-2.24-1-Large-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-GX-Production-2.24-1-Large-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-GX-Production-2.24-1-Large-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Tirade-GX-Production-2.24-1-Large-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Prices start at $2,499 for a frame only and $5,199 for a complete GX Eagle Build. There are also Shimano XT, SRAM XO Eagle Transmission, and XX Eagle Transmission builds, which top out at $9,599. Frames and select builds are available now directly from Revel, with full builds available in April. Revel is accepting preorders on builds that aren’t currently available with a $100 non-refundable deposit. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://revelbikes.com/product/Tirade/\" target=\"_blank\">revelbikes.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/revel-tirade-titanium-hardtail/\">Revel Tirade May Just Make You Fall in Love with Titanium Hardtails</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"e5652e49abbc74cc96fce80c5cf395eddd239796247de27e6c60c15bb954a054","category":"Cycling"}